{"title_page": "List of Tottenham Hotspur F.C. players", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{for|the current Tottenham first-team squad|Tottenham Hotspur F.C.#Squad}}\n[[image:Steve Perryman (1981).jpg|125px|thumb|upright|Steve Perryman holds the record of 854 appearances for Spurs.]]\nThis is a list ''' of notable [[association football|footballers]] who have played for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]''' since its foundation as '''Hotspur F.C.''' in 1882.\n\nThe list comprises those who have: -\n* made 100 or more first-team appearances for the club including substitutions, and/or\n* made 50 or more first-team and represented their country at full International level while on the club's books, and/or\n* achieved notability through making a major contribution to the club as a player, e.g. club captain, founder member or achieved notability in other ways, e.g {{sortname|Tony|Parks}}.\n\nRecords for some players vary from one data source to another and where possible these have been verified with reference to more than one such source. Corrections and updates should include a reference to source in the edit summary or on the Talk Page. To see a list of all Tottenham players, major or minor, with a Wikipedia article [[:Category:Tottenham Hotspur F.C. players]].\n\n==List of players==\n\n===Key===\n\nPlayers are listed according to the date of their first-team debut for the club.\nFirst team appearances include, [[Football League]], [[Premier League]], [[FA Cup]], [[Football League Cup|League Cup]], [[FA Community Shield]], [[UEFA Champions League]], [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]], [[Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]] and [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]. Substitute appearances are included. Wartime matches are excluded.\n\nInternational appearances are those at Full International level, including substitutions while on the club's books.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Positions\n|-\n!GK\n|[[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n!DF\n|[[Defender (football)|Defender]]\n!RB\n|[[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n!MF\n|[[Midfielder]]\n!RW\n|[[Midfielder#Winger|Right winger]]\n|-\n!CB\n|[[Defender (football)#Centre back|Central back]]\n!FB\n|[[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Fullback]]\n!LB\n|[[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left back]]\n!FW\n|[[Striker (association football)|Forward]]\n!LW\n|[[Midfielder#Winger|Left winger]]\n|-\n|}\n\n{{legend|#BDB76B|Tottenham Hotspur Greats or have been inducted into the club's Hall of Fame.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/spurs/History+of+the+Club/great-players.page|title=GREAT PLAYERS|publisher=www.tottenhamhotspur.com|accessdate=12 February 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722050240/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/spurs/History+of+the+Club/great-players.page |archivedate=22 July 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/hall-of-fame-41-legends-201114/ |title=HALL OF FAME - 41 LEGENDS|date= 20 November 2014 |work=Tottenham Hotspur }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/roberts-and-miller-set-for-hall-of-fame-280815/ |title=ROBERTS AND MILLER SET FOR HALL OF FAME |work=tottenhamhotspur.com |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=4 August 2016}}</ref>|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend|#FFDDFF|Players who have achieved notability through a major contribution to the club. |border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend|#faecc8|Club captains who have won a major senior competition.|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend|#98FB98|[[Tottenham Hotspur F.C. statistics|Club record holder]].|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\nAn asterisk (*) next to a name denotes that the player is still a current player at the club.\n\nThis is a list of '''notable''' players for Tottenham Hotspur. Please do not add the names and details of the current squad unless it meets the notability criteria above.\n\n===Table of notable players===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"tex