{"title_page": "FC Sf\u00e2ntul Gheorghe Suruceni", "text_new": "{{other uses|Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = FC Sf\u00e2ntul Gheorghe\n| image    = FC Sfintul gheorghe.png\n| upright  = 0.7\n| alt      = Logo\n| fullname = Fotbal Club Sf\u00e2ntul Gheorghe\n| nickname = \n| founded  = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2003|7|11}}\n| ground   = [[Suruceni Stadium|Suruceni]]\n| capacity = 1,500\n| owner = Valeriu Reni\u021b\u0103\n| chrtitle          = President\n| chairman = \n| mgrtitle = Head Coach\n| manager  = Serghei Cebotari\n| league   = [[Moldovan National Division|Divizia Na\u021bional\u0103]]\n| season   = [[2019 Moldovan National Division|2019]]\n| position = 2nd\n| current  = 2020 Moldovan National Division\n| pattern_la1 =\n| pattern_b1  = \n| pattern_ra1 =\n| leftarm1    = FF2020\n| body1       = FF2020\n| rightarm1   = FF2020\n| shorts1     = 2049B7\n| socks1      = FF2020\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2  =\n| pattern_ra2 =\n| leftarm2    = 000000\n| body2       = 800000\n| rightarm2   = 000000\n| shorts2     = 000000\n| socks2      = 000000\n}}\n\n'''FC Sf\u00e2ntul Gheorghe''' ({{IPA-ro|\u02c8sf\u0268ntul \u02c8\u0261e\u032for\u0261e}}; officially spelled ''Sf\u00eentul Gheorghe'') is a [[Moldova]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Suruceni]], [[Moldova]]. They play in the [[Moldovan National Division|Divizia Na\u021bional\u0103]], the top division in Moldovan football.\n\n==History==\nThe club was formed in 2003. Until 2007, it was represented by seven youth teams, aged 10\u201318 years. In 2007, the Under-18 team became the champion of The Republic of Moldova. In 2008\u20132009, the club decided to enter the second tier of Moldovan football, the [[Moldovan \"A\" Division|Divizia A]].\n\nIn 2009, due to an excellent infrastructure of two stadiums, one with [[artificial turf]] and another with natural turf, the club met all the licensing criteria and obtained the \"A\" licence, which allowed the team to play in the [[Moldovan National Division|Divizia Na\u021bional\u0103]].\n\n==League results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! Season\n! Div.\n! Pos.\n! Pl.\n! W\n! D\n! L\n! GS\n! GA\n! P\n![[Moldovan Cup|Cup]]\n!Top Scorer <br />(League)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2008\u201309 Moldovan \"A\" Division|2008\u201309]]\n|align=center|[[Moldovan \"A\" Division|2nd]]\n|align=center bgcolor=lightgreen|'''11'''\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|16\n|align=center|41\n|align=center|46\n|align=center|'''34'''\n|align=center|1/32\n|align=center|Unknown\n|-\n|align=center|[[2009\u201310 Moldovan National Division|2009\u201310]]\n|align=center rowspan = 3|'''[[Moldovan National Division|1st]]'''\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|align=center|33\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|21\n|align=center|29\n|align=center|67\n|align=center|'''24'''\n|align=center|1/16\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|MDA}} [[Mihai Pl\u0103tic\u0103]] (6)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2010\u201311 Moldovan National Division|2010\u201311]]\n|align=center|'''12'''\n|align=center|39\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|26\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|83\n|align=center|'''25'''\n|align=center|1/8\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|MDA}} [[Petru Ojog]] (4)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2011\u201312 Moldovan National Division|2011\u201312]]\n|align=center bgcolor=#FFCCCC|'''10'''\n|align=center|33\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|55\n|align=center|'''30'''\n|align=center|1/8\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|GHA}} [[Eric Sackey]] (7)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2012\u201313 Moldovan \"A\" Division|2012\u201313]]\n|align=center rowspan = 5|[[Moldovan \"A\" Division|2nd]]\n|align=center|'''8'''\n|align=center|28\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|38\n|align=center|51\n|align=center|'''40'''\n|align=center|1/16\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|MDA}} Alexandru \u021aurcan (7)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2013\u201314 Moldovan