oldovan football.\n\n==History==\nThe club was formed in 2003. Until 2007, it was represented by seven youth teams, aged 10\u201318 years. In 2007, the Under-18 team became the champion of The Republic of Moldova. In 2008\u20132009, the club decided to enter the second tier of Moldovan football, the [[Moldovan \"A\" Division|Divizia A]].\n\nIn 2009, due to an excellent infrastructure of two stadiums, one with [[artificial turf]] and another with natural turf, the club met all the licensing criteria and obtained the \"A\" licence, which allowed the team to play in the [[Moldovan National Division|Divizia Na\u021bional\u0103]].\n\n==League results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! Season\n! Div.\n! Pos.\n! Pl.\n! W\n! D\n! L\n! GS\n! GA\n! P\n![[Moldovan Cup|Cup]]\n!Top Scorer <br />(League)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2008\u201309 Moldovan \"A\" Division|2008\u201309]]\n|align=center|[[Moldovan \"A\" Division|2nd]]\n|align=center bgcolor=lightgreen|'''11'''\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|16\n|align=center|41\n|align=center|46\n|align=center|'''34'''\n|align=center|1/32\n|align=center|Unknown\n|-\n|align=center|[[2009\u201310 Moldovan National Division|2009\u201310]]\n|align=center rowspan = 3|'''[[Moldovan National Division|1st]]'''\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|align=center|33\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|21\n|align=center|29\n|align=center|67\n|align=center|'''24'''\n|align=center|1/16\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|MDA}} [[Mihai Pl\u0103tic\u0103]] (6)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2010\u201311 Moldovan National Division|2010\u201311]]\n|align=center|'''12'''\n|align=center|39\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|26\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|83\n|align=center|'''25'''\n|align=center|1/8\n|align=left|{{Flagicon|MDA}} [[Petru Ojog]] (4)\n|-\n|align=center|[[2011\u201312 Moldovan National Division|2011\u201312]]\n|align=center bgcolor=#FFCCCC|'''10'''\n|align=center|33\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|